19
00:00:44,390 --> 00:00:49,399
Don't be quiet with me.

20
00:00:49,399 --> 00:00:53,450
You know, someone has to take a blame for the losses.

21
00:00:53,450 --> 00:00:56,390
Touch me, Mason.

22
00:00:56,390 --> 00:01:01,859
You know, Chloe, I still think of you all the time.

23
00:01:01,859 --> 00:01:03,140
How about this?

24
00:01:03,140 --> 00:01:08,780
You be my mistress and I'll let your father out for a hook.

25
00:01:08,780 --> 00:01:15,359
You're sick, Mason.

26
00:01:15,359 --> 00:01:17,959
My hands are tied, then.

27
00:01:17,959 --> 00:01:21,640
My only suggestion, hire a very good lawyer,

28
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:23,359
because your father's looking at at least a decade

29
00:01:23,359 --> 00:01:26,140
behind bars.

30
00:01:26,140 --> 00:01:26,819
Oh, I'm sorry.

31
00:01:26,819 --> 00:01:27,659
I don't mean to laugh.

32
00:01:27,659 --> 00:01:30,379
It's just, who would actually dare to take your case

33
00:01:30,379 --> 00:01:31,819
and stay in my way?

34
00:01:31,819 --> 00:01:34,579
Remember, I'm marrying Sophia Foster, the daughter

35
00:01:34,579 --> 00:01:38,099
to only the richest family in town.

36
00:01:38,099 --> 00:01:41,969
Maybe her brother Ethan Foster is a brilliant attorney,

37
00:01:41,969 --> 00:01:43,049
but I don't think he's going to want

38
00:01:43,049 --> 00:01:47,420
to go to court against his future brother-in-law.

39
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:53,299
Ethan Foster, the guy I kissed,

40
00:01:53,299 --> 00:01:55,700
is he really the only one who could help me now?

